    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\r\n\r\n_No_\r\n\r\n### Feature description\r\n\r\nI use a piece of software called [Cursorless](https://github.com/cursorless-dev/cursorless) which enables efficient structural editing by defining a meta language for targeting elements which depends on always on text decorations. The decorations could be anything, but in practice they tend to be SVGs of different colors that are placed on top of characters to allow the user to reference a particular element with minimal work. Cursorless is most widely used by the voice coding community. See [this gif](https://github.com/cursorless-dev/cursorless/blob/1a0616521bbc6d264f22fdad41e9a7773f9b0bee/images/bringArgueAirAndEachAfterDrum.gif) for an example of what the text decorations look like.\r\n\r\nIt would be great if neovim GUIs could support this type of text decoration, but I imagine it will require some server side changes.\r\n\r\nCross linking some related issues for posterity:\r\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/1767\r\n- https://github.com/neovide/neovide/issues/1144\r\n- https://github.com/neovide/neovide/issues/669\r\n- https://github.com/neovide/neovide/issues/850\r\n\r\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
