        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I think cursorless support can be achieved using [unicode overscripts](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unicode_subscripts_and_superscripts) and background color on virtual text. \r\n\r\nHere is an example with quick command\r\n```\r\n:call nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, nvim_create_namespace(\"test\"), 0, 7, {'id':1, 'virt_text': [[\"o\\u0363\", 'IncSearch']], 'virt_text_pos':'overlay'})\r\n```\r\nThat produces:\r\n![Screenshot from 2024-04-13 21-47-02](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/10254532/17e02032-cd8d-4856-a91f-4740add22a91)\r\n\r\nThe only problem I see is that this limits you to a font with support for that character set, I'm using Julia Mono. Maybe a font patcher could be created that creates the current cursorless shapes.\r\n\r\n",
